<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<title>MKTG 4333 · Chapter 9 · Services deck</title>
<style>
  :root{
    --bg:#f5f2ec; --ink:#1a1a1a; --ink-soft:#4A4A4A; --ink-mute:#7A7A7A;
    --rule:#E8E6E1; --accent:#DA7756; --accent-tint:#FDF6F3;
    --font:'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
  }
  *{ margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
  html,body{ background:var(--bg); font-family:var(--font); color:var(--ink); }
  body{ padding:64px 72px 96px; }
  header{
    display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:flex-end;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule); padding-bottom:20px; margin-bottom:36px;
  }
  header .dot{ display:inline-block; width:10px; height:10px; background:var(--accent); border-radius:50%; margin-right:10px; vertical-align:middle; }
  header h1{ font-size:32px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-0.01em; }
  header h1 em{ font-style:italic; color:var(--accent); font-weight:500; }
  header .meta{
    font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--ink-mute); font-weight:600;
  }
  .intro{
    max-width:70ch; font-size:18px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom:44px;
  }
  .intro a{ color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; border-bottom:1px solid var(--accent); }
  .grid{
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(420px, 1fr));
    gap:28px;
  }
  .card{
    background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--rule);
    display:flex; flex-direction:column; overflow:hidden;
    transition: transform .2s, box-shadow .2s;
  }
  .card:hover{ transform:translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 24px -10px rgba(0,0,0,.15); }
  .card .frame{
    position:relative; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; overflow:hidden; background:#ffffff;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .card .frame .scaler{
    position:absolute; top:0; left:0;
    width:960px; height:540px;
    transform-origin: top left;
  }
  .card .frame iframe{
    width:960px; height:540px; border:0; display:block; pointer-events:none;
    background:#ffffff;
  }
  .card .info{ padding:16px 22px; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; }
  .card .info h3{ font-size:16px; font-weight:600; line-height:1.3; }
  .card .info .n{
    font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.14em; color:var(--ink-mute);
    text-transform:uppercase; white-space:nowrap;
  }
  .card .info .tmpl{ display:block; font-size:12px; color:var(--ink-soft); margin-top:3px; font-style:italic; }
  .card a.open{
    display:block; text-align:right; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:0.12em;
    text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--accent); font-weight:600;
    padding:0 22px 16px; text-decoration:none;
  }
  footer{
    margin-top:64px; padding-top:20px; border-top:1px solid var(--rule);
    font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-mute); display:flex; justify-content:space-between;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1><span class="dot"></span>Chapter 9 · <em>Services marketing</em>.</h1>
    <span class="meta">MKTG 4333 · 20 slides · 960 × 540</span>
  </header>

  <p class="intro">
    A teaching deck on services marketing, built on the coral design system. One claim per slide, white backgrounds,
    one coral element per slide, Segoe UI throughout. It runs the same arc as the Chapter 9 chapter: the buyer is inside
    the production, the four IIVP characteristics and the disciplines they force, the search-experience-credence spectrum,
    the seven Ps, the five SERVQUAL gaps and the RATER hierarchy, the service blueprint and its line of visibility, the
    moments of truth, and service recovery (the recovery effect, the three justices, the Ritz-Carlton cap), closing on
    four brand anchors (Singapore Airlines, Costco, Patagonia, Mayo Clinic). Read the system rules in
    <a href="../DESIGN-SYSTEM.md">DESIGN-SYSTEM.md</a> and
    <a href="../CHART-PRINCIPLES.md">CHART-PRINCIPLES.md</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="grid" id="grid"></div>

<script>
(() => {
  const slides = [
    ["01-title.html",               "01", "Services marketing", "Title / cover"],
    ["02-divider-buyer-inside.html","02", "The buyer is on the factory floor", "Section divider"],
    ["03-iivp.html",                "03", "Each of the four IIVP traits forces one discipline", "Content · four traits"],
    ["04-search-credence.html",     "04", "The further right a purchase sits, the more the buyer leans on cues", "Exhibit · chapter spectrum"],
    ["05-seven-ps.html",            "05", "Services add three Ps once the buyer is in the room", "Two-column"],
    ["06-divider-gaps.html",        "06", "The buyer feels only one of five gaps", "Section divider"],
    ["07-gaps-model.html",          "07", "The firm closes the four it cannot see to close the one the buyer feels", "Exhibit · chapter SERVQUAL"],
    ["08-rater.html",               "08", "Firms spend most on the dimension that moves judgment least", "Comparison bars"],
    ["09-klarna-amazon.html",       "09", "An AI front door could not safely own the recovery encounter", "Two-column"],
    ["10-divider-blueprint.html",   "10", "An invisible service cannot be fixed", "Section divider"],
    ["11-blueprint.html",           "11", "The five swimlanes split at the line of visibility", "Exhibit · service blueprint"],
    ["12-journey-vs-blueprint.html","12", "The blueprint is the journey map plus the backstage", "Two-column"],
    ["13-moments-of-truth.html",    "13", "SAS funded the front line ahead of assets the buyer never sees", "Content · the arithmetic"],
    ["14-divider-recovery.html",    "14", "A good recovery can beat no failure at all", "Section divider"],
    ["15-recovery-effect.html",     "15", "A well-resolved failure is associated with more loyalty than no problem", "Comparison bars"],
    ["16-three-justices.html",      "16", "The conversation outweighs the compensation amount", "Content · three justices"],
    ["17-ritz-carnival.html",       "17", "A recovery has to match the shape of the failure", "Two-column"],
    ["18-recovery-quote.html",      "18", "Compensation buys the resolution; the conversation buys the relationship", "Pull quote"],
    ["19-four-brands.html",         "19", "Four brands, each through the discipline a different trait forces", "KPI row"],
    ["20-closing.html",             "20", "Run the chapter's four moves on a real service you use", "Closing / takeaways"]
  ];
  const grid = document.getElementById('grid');
  slides.forEach(([href, n, claim, tmpl]) => {
    const card = document.createElement('article');
    card.className = 'card';
    card.innerHTML =
      '<div class="frame"><div class="scaler"><iframe src="' + href + '?thumb=1" title="' + claim + '"></iframe></div></div>' +
      '<div class="info"><div><h3>' + claim + '</h3><span class="tmpl">' + tmpl + '</span></div><span class="n">' + n + '</span></div>' +
      '<a class="open" href="' + href + '" target="_blank">Open &rarr;</a>';
    grid.appendChild(card);
  });

  function fitCards(){
    document.querySelectorAll('.card .frame').forEach(frame => {
      const scaler = frame.querySelector('.scaler');
      if (!scaler) return;
      const w = frame.clientWidth;
      const s = w / 960;
      scaler.style.transform = 'scale(' + s + ')';
      scaler.style.width  = '960px';
      scaler.style.height = '540px';
      frame.style.height = (540 * s) + 'px';
    });
  }
  document.querySelectorAll('iframe').forEach(f => {
    f.addEventListener('load', () => {
      try { f.contentDocument.documentElement.classList.add('is-thumb'); } catch(_){}
    });
  });
  window.addEventListener('resize', fitCards);
  window.addEventListener('load', fitCards);
  fitCards();
})();
</script>

  <footer>
    <span>MKTG 4333 · Prof. Felipe M. Affonso · Spears School of Business</span>
    <span>White bg · Segoe UI · one coral accent · pairs with the Ch 9 chapter</span>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
